HEADWORD: Orthopedical
<hw>Or`tho*ped"ic*al</hw>
<pr>(?)</pr>, }</mhw> <pos>a.</pos> <fld>(Med.)</fld> <def>Of,
pertaining to, or employed in, orthopedics; relating to the prevention
or cure of deformities of children, or, in general, of the human body at
any age; <as>as, <ex>orthopedic</ex> surgery; an <ex>orthopedic</ex>
hospital.</as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

